modules.description: Provides monadic and applicative combinators for constructing parsers that process byte streams, with support for backtracking, lookahead, and zero-copy I/O. Works with input sources such as buffers and streams, enabling precise control over data consumption. Used to implement protocol parsers like HTTP and JSON, where performance and accuracy are critical.

Parses binary data from an input channel using a custom parser, returning parsed values and unconsumed buffer state. Operates on in_channel and parser definitions built with Angstrom combinators. Processes streaming data such as network protocols or binary file formats efficiently.
